: Maximum Points You Can Obtain from Cards
ğŸ”¹ Problem: https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-points-you-can-obtain-from-cards/

Pick exactly k cards from the beginning or end of the array cardPoints.
Return the maximum score possible.

âœ… Approach: Prefix + Suffix Sum (O(k))
ğŸ”¸ Idea

Start by taking all k cards from the left side.

Then gradually replace some left cards with cards from the right side.

Keep track of the maximum score.

ğŸ”¸ Example

cardPoints = [1,2,3,4,5,6,1], k = 3

Take first 3 â†’ sum = 1+2+3 = 6

Replace last left card with rightmost â†’ 1+2+1 = 4

Replace last 2 left cards with 2 from right â†’ 1+6+1 = 8

Replace all 3 with right side â†’ 5+6+1 = 12 âœ…

Answer = 12

ğŸ”¸ C++ Code
class Solution {
public:
    int maxScore(vector<int>& cardPoints, int k) {
        int sum = 0, maxsum = 0;
        
        // Take all k from left initially
        for (int i = 0; i < k; i++) {
            sum += cardPoints[i];
            maxsum = max(maxsum, sum);
        }

        int n = cardPoints.size();
        // Gradually replace left picks with right picks
        for (int i = n - 1; i >= n - k; i--) {
            sum = sum + cardPoints[i] - cardPoints[i - (n - k)];
            maxsum = max(maxsum, sum);
        }

        return maxsum;
    }
};

âœ… Complexity

Time: O(k)

Space: O(1)

âš¡ Memory Hook:
ğŸ‘‰ â€œTake k from left, then swap with right one by one â†’ keep max.â€
